{{Politics of Egypt}}

'''Elections for the [[Shura Council]]''', the upper house of the [[Parliament of Egypt|Egyptian parliament]], were held in [[Egypt]] on 1 June and 8 June 2010.<ref name="2010 UPCOMING ELECTIONS">[http://www.mherrera.org/elections.htm 2010 UPCOMING ELECTIONS]</ref><ref name="IFES Election Guide">[http://www.electionguide.org/country.php?ID=65 IFES Election Guide]</ref> From a total of 264 seats 88 are up for election every three years, another 44 are appointed by the [[President of Egypt|president]]. Out of 446 candidates for elections, 115 are from political parties and 331 are independents.<ref>{{cite web|title=Shura Council elections to kick off Tuesday |url=http://www.almasryalyoum.com/en/news/shura-council-elections-kick-tuesday|publisher=Al Masry Al Youm|accessdate=1 June 2010}}</ref>

